# Betrimex Fabric Demo — Data Dictionary

**Version:** 1.0
**Source layer:** Bronze (raw synthetic CSVs in `01_data/raw/`)
**Owner:** Therese Sario, Microsoft Philippines
**Customer:** Betrimex (Ben Tre Trading & Import-Export JSC) — Vietnamese coconut processor, brand Cocoxim

---

## Entity Relationship Overview

```
       farmers (1) ──< lots (M) ──< lot_consumption (M) >── (1) production_runs
                                                                  │
                                                                  ├── (M) quality_tests
                                                                  │
                                                                  └── (M) sales_orders
```

**Key relationships**

- 1 farmer → many lots
- Many lots → many production runs (via `lot_consumption` bridge)
- 1 production run → many quality tests
- 1 production run → many sales orders

The `lot_consumption` bridge enables **lot-level traceability** — the ability to trace any Cocoxim bottle back to the specific smallholder farmer(s) whose coconuts went into it. Critical for organic certification audits (EU Organic, USDA Organic).

