## 2. `lots.csv` — Coconut Lot Deliveries

**Description:** Every batch of coconuts a farmer delivers to a collection point. The foundational supply data.

**Grain:** One row per delivery.
**Primary key:** `lot_id`
**Foreign keys:** `farmer_id` → `farmers.farmer_id`

| Column | Type | Nullable | Description | Example | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| `lot_id` | String | No | Unique lot identifier | `LOT-0000001` | Zero-padded sequence. Used as FK in `lot_consumption`. |
| `farmer_id` | Integer | No | Reference to delivering farmer | `12345` | FK to `farmers`. |
| `intake_date` | Date (YYYY-MM-DD) | No | Date the lot was received at the collection point | `2025-08-14` | Spans ~2 years of history. Use for time-series analysis. |
| `collection_point` | String | No | The Betrimex hub where the farmer delivered | `Mo Cay Nam Hub` | Always within the farmer's district. 17 distinct hubs across 4 provinces. |
| `district` | String | No | Province the lot came from | `Ben Tre` | Denormalized from farmer for query performance. |
| `weight_kg` | Float | No | Net weight of the coconuts in this lot | `213.5` | Range ~50–500 kg, mode ~180 kg (typical smallholder delivery size). |
| `brix` | Float | No | Sugar content of the coconut water in this lot | `6.21` | Range 3.5–8.5 °Bx. Mean ~6.0. Critical quality driver — low brix → low yield. |
| `grade` | String | No | Quality grade assigned at intake | `A`, `B`, `C` | Distribution ~60% A / 30% B / 10% C overall. Organic farms skew higher. |
| `is_organic` | Boolean | No | Whether this lot came from an organic-certified farmer | `True`, `False` | Denormalized from farmer for fast filtering. |

**Business notes**

- `brix` and `grade` are the two main quality drivers — Data Agent uses these to explain yield variance.
- `intake_date` is the single most important date for time-series queries.
- The combination of (`farmer_id`, `intake_date`) is effectively unique for natural-key joins.

