## 3. `production_runs.csv` — Processing Batches

**Description:** Every batch of Cocoxim product processed on a specific plant line. Links input (lots) to output (bottles/packages).

**Grain:** One row per production run.
**Primary key:** `run_id`

| Column | Type | Nullable | Description | Example | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| `run_id` | String | No | Unique run identifier | `RUN-000123` | Zero-padded sequence. Used as FK in `quality_tests`, `sales_orders`, `lot_consumption`. |
| `plant` | String | No | Manufacturing plant where the run occurred | `Ben Tre Main Plant` | One of 3 plants: Main, Organic, New Facility. |
| `line` | String | No | Specific production line within the plant | `Line 1`, `Line 2` | Each plant has 2–4 lines. |
| `product` | String | No | Cocoxim SKU produced in this run | `Cocoxim Coconut Water Original 330ml` | Real-ish SKU naming. ~15 distinct products. |
| `shift` | String | No | Production shift | `Morning`, `Afternoon`, `Night` | 8-hour shifts. |
| `start_datetime` | Datetime | No | When the run started | `2025-08-14 06:15:00` | Local time. |
| `end_datetime` | Datetime | No | When the run completed | `2025-08-14 14:42:00` | `start_datetime + duration_hours`. |
| `duration_hours` | Float | No | Run duration | `8.45` | Typical 4–12 hours. |
| `input_weight_kg` | Float | No | Total raw coconut input consumed | `28450.0` | Sum of `weight_kg` across consumed lots. |
| `expected_yield` | Float | No | Theoretical output given input and product type | `11949.0` | Liters for water/milk, kg for desiccated/oil. |
| `actual_yield` | Float | No | Real output measured at end of run | `10260.3` | Always ≤ `expected_yield`. |
| `yield_pct` | Float | No | actual / expected × 100 | `85.86` | Range ~55–99%. Mean ~85%. The headline KPI. |
| `avg_brix` | Float | No | Weighted average brix of consumed lots | `6.18` | Quality input signal. |
| `grade_a_pct` | Float | No | Percentage of consumed lots that were Grade A | `62.40` | Quality input signal. |
| `downtime_minutes` | Integer | No | Total downtime during the run | `35` | Most runs <30 min; 5% have major events (60–240 min). |
| `is_organic_run` | Boolean | No | Whether this run produced an organic SKU | `True`, `False` | Driven by which plant + product. |
| `num_lots_consumed` | Integer | No | Number of distinct lots used in this run | `127` | Range 50–200. |

**Business notes**

- `yield_pct` is the single most important manufacturing KPI — the Data Agent should treat it as the primary measure.
- Low `avg_brix` or low `grade_a_pct` are the two most common drivers when `yield_pct` underperforms.
- Use `is_organic_run` to filter for organic-traceability questions.
- Use this table as `fact_production_run` in the Gold layer.

