## 5. `quality_tests.csv` — QA Test Results

**Description:** Quality assurance test results performed during and after each production run.

**Grain:** One row per test execution.
**Primary key:** `test_id`
**Foreign key:** `run_id` → `production_runs.run_id`

| Column | Type | Nullable | Description | Example | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| `test_id` | String | No | Unique test execution identifier | `QT-00000001` | Zero-padded sequence. |
| `run_id` | String | No | Production run the test was performed on | `RUN-000123` | FK to `production_runs`. |
| `test_name` | String | No | Specific QA test performed | `Brix`, `pH`, `Total Plate Count` | 10 distinct tests. |
| `category` | String | No | Test category | `Chemical`, `Microbiological`, `Physical` | Used for category-level pass/fail rollups. |
| `value` | Float | No | Measured test value | `6.18`, `45.2` | Unit varies by test (see `unit`). |
| `target` | Float | No | Target spec for the test | `6.0` | Same unit as `value`. |
| `tolerance` | Float | No | Acceptable +/- variance from target | `1.0` | Inside [target−tolerance, target+tolerance] = Pass. |
| `unit` | String | No | Measurement unit | `°Bx`, `pH`, `CFU/mL`, `mg/L`, `mL`, `cP`, `L*` | Display unit for the value. |
| `pass_fail` | String | No | Whether the test passed spec | `Pass`, `Fail` | ~90% Pass overall. |
| `test_datetime` | Datetime | No | When the test was performed | `2025-08-14 09:32:00` | During or shortly after the run. |

### Test catalog

| test_name | category | Target | Unit | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| `Brix` | Chemical | 6.0 ±1.0 | °Bx | Sugar / sweetness |
| `pH` | Chemical | 5.2 ±0.4 | pH | Acidity |
| `Sodium` | Chemical | 105 ±25 | mg/L | Mineral content |
| `Potassium` | Chemical | 250 ±50 | mg/L | Mineral content |
| `Total Plate Count` | Microbiological | ≤100 ±200 | CFU/mL | Bacterial load |
| `Yeast & Mold` | Microbiological | ≤10 ±20 | CFU/mL | Fungal load |
| `Coliform` | Microbiological | 0 ±1 | CFU/mL | Contamination indicator |
| `Color L*` | Physical | 92 ±4 | L* | CIE Lab lightness |
| `Viscosity` | Physical | 1.2 ±0.3 | cP | Thickness |
| `Fill Volume` | Physical | 330 ±5 | mL | Package fill accuracy |

**Business notes**

- Failure rates correlate with low input quality (low brix, low Grade A %).
- Microbiological failures are the most serious from a compliance standpoint.

